	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This spell can be good and bad.&nbsp;&nbsp;It sets up a field around you so that if something walks into the field, you will be notified before it gets to you.  I don't know the range offhand, but it's supposed to be helpful when you're medding and can't see what's happening around you.  The bad part is that while the effect is active, you will basically be spamming others in your area as they continually get the message "you get the feeling you are being watched" or something to that effect.  This continues much like the messages that you get during a bard song, like every few seconds.  It can be annoying and there have been reports (I have not confirmed) that this spamming has caused tremendous lag in certain areas.  Ohterwise the weapon itself is pretty cool.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
